{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"halfcrazed-sylphlike-salmon","description":"## Why\nTHE security-critical divergence. e165 (change 563) implemented key validity as an\n**HLC-epoch** window (ordinal position in the reducer's canonical replay). The\nAPPROVED epic design requires **git-commit-ancestry** validity (tickets-branch commit\nSHAs). HLC ordering is partly author-assigned, so a malicious clone holding a\nlater-revoked key can write an event with a backdated HLC that sorts BEFORE the\nrevocation and verifies as valid — defeating the feature's core \"not\nattacker-controllable\" promise. The immutable commit DAG closes that hole. This story\ntransitions the delivered HLC-epoch model to the approved commit-ancestry model.\n(User rejected the delivered design; see session_log d7c0.)\n\n## Why the DAG is stronger (record the rationale)\nCommit SHAs chain content+parents, so an event's position in history is a tamper-proof\nfact — you cannot make a new event an ancestor of an existing revocation commit without\nforging SHAs. HLC ordering trusts the author-assigned timestamp component; commit\nancestry trusts only the DAG.\n\n## What\nReplace the epoch-based keyring with a commit-anchored one:\n- A key record binds `{pubkey, added_at_commit, revoked_at_commit?}` where the values\n  are **tickets-branch commit SHAs** (the commit that introduced the KEY_ADD /\n  KEY_REVOKE event). Drop `added_epoch`/`revoked_epoch`/`keyring_epoch`.\n- **Event->commit resolution** (the core challenge): the reducer replays event FILES,\n  but a commit SHA is git metadata, not in the event JSON. Provide a resolver that\n  maps a KEY event (and an event under verification) to its tickets-branch commit SHA\n  (e.g. `git log --diff-filter=A --format=%H -- <event-file-path>` for the introducing\n  commit, or a batched log walk). Cache per run.\n- **Validity rule:** an event signed by key K verifies iff the event's tickets-branch\n  commit is a DESCENDANT of `K.added_at_commit` AND NOT a descendant of\n  `K.revoked_at_commit` (git DAG: `git merge-base --is-ancestor`). Replace\n  `verify_authorship_at_epoch` / `epoch_for_position` with commit-ancestry equivalents\n  (`verify_authorship_at_commit`).\n- Keep: TOFU genesis (first key-add accepted only when self-signed), unsigned\n  non-genesis key-add refused, signed add/rotate/revoke, replay-never-rejects.\n- Reducer keyring fold + `make_initial_state` seed + snapshot restore updated to the\n  commit-anchored records (no epoch counter to freeze). Bump reducer/cache versions.\n- Consumes TS1's in-toto authorship (verify against the identity's keys valid at the\n  event's commit).\n\n## Scope\nIn: the commit-anchored key records, event->commit resolution, DAG-ancestry validity,\nthe write-gate (signed rotation, TOFU), reducer fold + snapshot. Out: authorship\npayload format (TS1), the ledger schema + verdict (TS3 / 3183). NOTE: e165's delivered\nHLC-epoch code (verify_authorship_at_epoch, epoch_for_position, keyring_epoch,\nepoch fields) is REMOVED/REPLACED here.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Each identity key record binds `{pubkey, added_at_commit, revoked_at_commit?}`\n  (tickets-branch commit SHAs); a test using TWO fixture commits on the tickets branch\n  asserts the record shape.\n- [ ] Genesis key-add is accepted ONLY when self-signed (TOFU base case); an unsigned\n  NON-genesis key-add is refused (test).\n- [ ] An event whose commit is NOT a descendant of the key's `added_at_commit` (or IS a\n  descendant of its `revoked_at_commit`) FAILS verification; one that IS a descendant of\n  `added_at_commit` and NOT of `revoked_at_commit` PASSES (test with the two fixture\n  commits, both sides of the boundary).\n- [ ] Validity derives from commit ancestry, NOT event timestamps: a backdated `data`\n  timestamp does not change which commit governs the event (test).\n- [ ] Replay never rejects: a bad-signature/invalid-era event still folds into state\n  (test); the delivered HLC-epoch surface (verify_authorship_at_epoch, keyring_epoch)\n  is gone (grep-asserted absent).\n\n## file_impact\n- `src/rebar/attest/authorship.py` (verify_authorship_at_commit + commit-ancestry trust root; remove _at_epoch)\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (commit-anchored keyring fold; remove epoch counter)\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_state.py` + `_version.py` + `_cache.py` (keyring shape + version bumps)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/identity.py` (add/revoke key seam records commit SHAs; event->commit resolver)","id":"09f9-f66c-9748-48e5","parent_id":"e68d-b701-4dd9-47aa","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"transition: key validity -> git-commit-ancestry (tickets-branch SHAs, replaces HLC-epoch)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783879560810767001,"uuid":"f9e4a463-3013-4ec4-a278-3f3c828a4211"}